description:
CK4$IIAM Ended not OK_NO_CALL JOB NodeID: AUL1:
 Component : AUL1
close_notes:
Hi All,
In CK4 PROD Cycle (Odate ï¿½ 02/24/23), Job CK4$IIAM failed at STEP0010 with MAXCC=0008.
 
As per spool :
STOR4B FDRR94** UNABLE TO ALLOCATE TARGET DATASET-COMP=04,CODE=0210,INFO=0000,DS
STOR4B IKJ56225I DATA SET CK4.VSAM.BASEOL.SYSSTATA ALREADY IN USE, TRY LATER+   
STOR4B IKJ56225I DATA SET IS ALLOCATED TO ANOTHER JOB OR USER                   
STOR4B IEFA110I DATA SET CONTENTION                                             
STOR4B DATA SET CK4.VSAM.BASEOL.SYSSTATA IN USE BY                              
STOR4B SYSNAME  JOBNAME  ASID                                                   
STOR4B AUL1     CICSE    0061                                                   
STOR4B FDRR32** BACKUP PROCESSING TERMINATED                                    
STOR4B FDRR33** BACKUP   FAILED - CODE=00008,DSN=CK4.VSAM.BASEOL.SYSSTATA  

STOR5C FDRR94** UNABLE TO ALLOCATE TARGET DATASET-COMP=04,CODE=0210,INFO=0000,DS
STOR5C IKJ56225I DATA SET CK4.VSAM.BASEOL.AUXSEG1$ ALREADY IN USE, TRY LATER+   
STOR5C IKJ56225I DATA SET IS ALLOCATED TO ANOTHER JOB OR USER                   
STOR5C IEFA110I DATA SET CONTENTION                                             
STOR5C DATA SET CK4.VSAM.BASEOL.AUXSEG1$ IN USE BY                              
STOR5C SYSNAME  JOBNAME  ASID                                                   
STOR5C AUL1     CICSE    0061                                                   
STOR5C FDRR32** BACKUP PROCESSING TERMINATED                                    
STOR5C FDRR33** BACKUP   FAILED - CODE=00008,DSN=CK4.VSAM.BASEOL.AUXSEG1$            
                    
                                                
 
Analysis :    
Job failed for datasets "CK4.VSAM.BASEOL.AUXSEG1$" and "CK4.VSAM.BASEOL.SYSSTATA" as it was in use by the other job at the time of execution. The files got attached to CICSE region. 
 
Resolution :
 
1. We closed the files from CICSE region.
2. Asked OPS team to re-run the job from 'TOP'.
3) Open the files once job completed fine.
 
Job Ended-OK with above resolution.

Document  : SCHD.CTM.DOC                        
 
Thanks and Regards
Shailendra Singh
short_description: PCD- CK4\$IIAM Ended not OK_NO_CALL JOB NodeID: AUL1

 Component : AUL1
close_notes:
ALIS prod cycle job ALIS0050 was abended in 01/30/2023 night's production cycle in STEP0001 due to S0C7 error.
 
Problem description: As per the spool ï¿½ 
A system abend 0C7 reason code X'0' occurred in module ALISOA CSECT X016SECT at
offset X'564'.                                                                 
A program-interruption code 0007 (Data Exception) is associated with this abend
 
Resolution:
 Problem policy # ï¿½ 016127255900
ï¿½	We found out the current policy number in file ' ALIS.FM.OUT.MESS.OMESS.DISK' as 016127255900, done unit testing  by removing policy.
ï¿½	As ALIS0030 was scheduled in last night's cycle, we had OPS run the job ALIS6203 to delete the abending policy.
ï¿½	Before running the job ALIS6203, deleted (renamed) the following files using firecall ID as these files were used in jobs ALIS0030 and ALIS0050 - 
Renamed the files - 
ALIS.MASTER.FILE.AMAST(0)
ALIS.MASTER.EXT.FILE.AMAST(0)
ALIS.FM.OUT.MESS.OMESS.DISK
ALIS.UPDATED.POL.UPPOL.DISK
ALIS.PERS.FM.EXTRACTS.APFE
ALIS.ZERO.GUMLABEL

To - 
 
     TEST.ALIS.FM.OUT.MESS.OMESS.DISK.P013023  
TEST.ALIS.MASTER.EXT.FILE.AMAST.P013023 
TEST.ALIS.MASTER.FILE.AMAST.P013023 
TEST.ALIS.PERS.FM.EXTRACTS.APFE.P013023 
TEST.ALIS.UPDATED.POL.UPPOL.DISK.P013023 
TEST.ALIS.ZERO.GUMLABEL.P013023  
  
 Requested PCD to run the job ALIS6203 from the library - PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT(ALIS6203) with the following overrides - 
 
//ALIS6230 EXEC PROC=ALIS6203,                                
//         DELREC=16127255900,16YYYYYYY00,16ZZZZZZZ00'       
//STEP0020.SYS004 DD *                                        
 POL= 016127255900     CHANGE POLICY # ON THIS CARD - 12 DIGITS  
 
ï¿½	Requested PCD to rerun the job ALIS0030.
ï¿½	Requested PCD to rerun the job ALIS0050. 
Job ALIS0050 ended Ok with the above resolution. 

Incident - INC0712371
Firecall ID used:- P1SVBB

close_notes:
In Production PPlus VCS Cycle (ODATE ï¿½ 01/12/2023), Job VCS$0111 abended at PS60 with ABEND S0C7.
                                                                     
Abending Policy:
G37824ï¿½ Found based on the Instructions given in the below VCS$0111 abend notes.
\\slpfle01.oneamerica.com\vol_tm\Enterprise Compensation Tech Ref\On Call and Support Documentation\PPLUS  --- VCS$0111 Abend. 
Solution:
1.	Checked the file VCS.PPL.PPLUSHCH, with HEX ON to see where numeric zeros are missing compared to adjacent rows. The policy number on the row where numeric zeros are missing should match the policy number found in IDIREPRT.
2.	Updated 9 sets of packed fields starting at column 114 (each set is made up of 4 numeric fields 3 bytes long, each denoted by the "C") and another 9 sets starting at column 394 using Fire call ID : TA04092
3.	Asked PCD to rerun the job from the top.
 
To Avoid VCS$0500 Job abend -
 
1.	Updated VarChar column:  TRANSACTION_IMAGE in PPLUS02.DSRPTRG table as the transaction is also available in this column.
2.	Updated 9 sets of packed fields starting at off-set 629 (each set is made up of 4 numeric fields 3 bytes long, each denoted by the "C") and another 9 sets starting at off-set 909 with numeric hex values by overlaying the spaces using Fire call ID : TA04092.

description:
Analysis ï¿½  When we checked abended job we found that JSTEP020(CLPNDPOL) ULTIM program was rejected and job continued to execute with the next steps again at JSTEP050(CLANNULT) ULTIM program was rejected due to the missing of a period in the SET statement of CLANNULT ULTIM and again continued to execute and job failed at JSTEP090 due to mismatch of Record Length and Block Size of Sort Out file with Sort In file. In the next re-run, the job failed at JSTEP110 due to the missing DD statement for file CKFRECNB in the PROC.
solution-

1.	JSTEP020(CLPNDPOL): The copybook CKFRECTR was not defined in the PROD.CL.CARDLIB(UDPOLICY) ? We have given the override of TEST.CL.CARDLIB(UDPOLICY) in the JCL.

2.	JSTEP050(CLANNULT): A period was missing in the SET statement of the ULTIM: PROD.CL.ULTIM(CLANNULT) -> We have given the override of TEST.CL.ULTIM(CLANNULT) in the JCL.

3.	JSTEP090: The output file's Record Length & Block Size has been updated to 231 & 27720 

4.	JSTEP110: This DD statement was missing - //STEP0010.CKFRECNB DD  DUMMY -> We have provided the override in the JCL.

Made all these changes and ran the Job from PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT library and it got completed.

Firecall used : P1SVBB
Added restart instruction to start from RESTART=JSTEP020.STEP0010 in PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT library.
close_notes: All changes have been moved to PROD under CHG0079314. Hence, CL$$8004 will not abend in the next run.
short_description: PCD- CL\$\$8004 ENDED NOT OK_NO_CALL JOB NodeID: AUL1

description:
Please find Fire call usage details below:

a. The reason for the change - SLRP0010 Job failure

c. The date the change was made - 12/01/22
d. The File that was updated - PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT
close_notes:
Hi All,

In last night's SLRP Prod cycle (11/30/2022), Job SLRP0010 abended with a user abend S0C7 at STEP0050.
                                                                                                                                     
Message from spool:

+IDI0002I Module W710033, program W710033, offset X'6DDA': Abend S0C7 (Data Exception)
+IDI0003I Fault ID F22935 assigned in history file SYS2.FA.HIST.BATCH          

Abending Record:

2527009998BURCHELL,WILLIAM,R,JR.*

Solution:
ï¿½	Copied the SLRP input file SLRP.SRT.CHK.ACCTG.CMB.SLSRT.G6348V00 into test file TEST.SLRP.SRT.CHK.ACCTG.CMB.SLSRT.D1201.
ï¿½	As per SCHD.CTM.DOC, bypassed the abending record from the backup-up file.
ï¿½	Copied the job into PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT, added restart instruction RESTART=SLRP0010.STEP0050 in the job card and GDG overrides GDG07='0', GDGKM='0', and GDG08='0' in the exec statement along with the below input file override:
//STEP0050.ICAFLE18 DD DSN=TEST.SLRP.SRT.CHK.ACCTG.CMB.SLSRT.D1201,
//             DISP=(OLD,KEEP,KEEP)                                
ï¿½	Asked the PCD operations team to rerun job SLRP0010 from PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT library.
ï¿½	Job-Ended-OK with the above resolution.

description:
Firecall ID: TA04092 used for resolving abend in CL$$0012
a) Taken the backup of CL.BKUP.FUND.PRICES(0) as CL.CKUP.FUND.PRICES.D112922
b) Deleted the duplicate record from GDG
c) The GDG was modified on 11/29/2022.
close_notes:
In CyberLife PROD cycle (Odate ï¿½ 11/29/22) Job CL$$0012 got abended at STEP0050 due to ABENDU0001.
 
From STEP0040 SYSUT2 :-

                    FUND ID     SEV             ERROR DESCRIPTION               
                    ____________________________________________________________
                                1...+...10....+...20....+...30....+...40....+...
                    SPFND2      V00SPFND210011112420221128202204027262183       
                                 2  FF0018 - INPUT DATE RANGE INVALID           
                                        LAST VALUATION DATE NOT LESS THAN LOW DATE RANGE DATE
                                

Analysis: In fund prices file we found that the SPFND2 had two entries and one was duplicate from yesterday's file so edited the file and removed that duplicate SPFND2 entry. 

 
Solution :-
 
1) Took the backup of  ' CL.BKUP.FUND.PRICES.G5938V00' as 'CL.BKUP.FUND.PRICES.D112922'.
 
2) Removed the duplicate SPFND2 entry from original file using Fire call ID: TA04092.

3) Had PCD to run the restore Job CL$$R012.

4) Informed OPS to rerun the job CL$$0012 from TOP after completion of CL$$R012.
 
Job Ended-OK with the above resolution.

description:
Used Fire call: TA04092 for resolving abend in VCS$0111
1) Updated the file: VCS.PPL.PPLUSHCH
2) Updated VarChar column:  TRANSACTION_IMAGE in PPLUS02.DSRPTRG table
The date change was made is 10/25/2022
close_notes:
Hi All,
In Production PPlus VCS Cycle (ODATE - 10/24/2022), Job VCS$0111 abended at PS60 with ABEND S0C7.
As per Spool:
A system abend 0C7 occurred in module UNPACKP2 program PPLSUNP2 at offset      
X'3774'.                                                                       
Abending Policy:
G38166 ï¿½  Found based on the Instructions given in the below VCS$0111 abend notes.
\\slpfle01.oneamerica.com\vol_tm\Enterprise Compensation Tech Ref\On Call and Support Documentation\PPLUS  --- VCS$0111 Abend. 
Solution:
1.	Checked the file VCS.PPL.PPLUSHCH, with HEX ON to see where numeric zeros are missing compared to adjacent rows. The policy number on the row where numeric zeros are missing should match the policy number found in IDIREPRT.
2.	Updated 9 sets of packed fields starting at column 114 (each set is made up of 4 numeric fields 3 bytes long, each denoted by the "C") and another 9 sets starting at column 394 using Fire call ID : TA04092
3.	Asked PCD to rerun the job from the top.

Incident number - INC0684548 
 
To Avoid VCS$0500 Job abend -
 
1.	Updated VarChar column:  TRANSACTION_IMAGE in PPLUS02.DSRPTRG table as the transaction is also available in this column.
2.	Updated 9 sets of packed fields starting at off-set 629 (each set is made up of 4 numeric fields 3 bytes long, each denoted by the "C") and another 9 sets starting at off-set 909 with numeric hex values by overlaying the spaces using Fire call ID : TA04092.

Jobs have Ended-OK with above resolution.

Thanks,
Harindra
short_description: PCD- VCS\$0111 Ended not OK_NO_CALL JOB NodeID: AUL1

close_notes:
Hi All,  
 
ALIS prod cycle job ALIS0050 was abended in 09/06/2022 night's production cycle in STEP0001 due to S0C7 error.
 
Problem description: As per the spool ï¿½ 
A system abend 0C7 reason code X'0' occurred in module ALISOA CSECT X016SECT at
offset X'564'.                                                                 
A program-interruption code 0007 (Data Exception) is associated with this abend
 
Resolution:
 Problem policy # ï¿½ 18000069200
ï¿½	We found out the current policy number in file ' ALIS.FM.OUT.MESS.OMESS.DISK' as 18000069200, done unit testing  by removing policy.
ï¿½	As ALIS0030 was scheduled in last night's cycle, we had OPS run the job ALIS6203 to delete the abending policy.
ï¿½	Before running the job ALIS6203, deleted (renamed) the following files using firecall ID as these files were used in jobs ALIS0030 and ALIS0050 - 
Renamed the files - 
ALIS.MASTER.FILE.AMAST(0)
ALIS.MASTER.EXT.FILE.AMAST(0)
ALIS.FM.OUT.MESS.OMESS.DISK
ALIS.UPDATED.POL.UPPOL.DISK
ALIS.PERS.FM.EXTRACTS.APFE
ALIS.ZERO.GUMLABEL

To - 
 
ALIS.MASTER.FILE.AMAST.D090622
ALIS.MASTER.EXT.FILE.AMAST.D090622
ALIS.FM.OUT.MESS.OMESS.DISK.D090622
ALIS.UPDATED.POL.UPPOL.DISK.D090622
ALIS.PERS.FM.EXTRACTS.APFE.D090622
ALIS.ZERO.GUMLABEL.D090622

 Requested PCD to run the job ALIS6203 from the library - PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT(ALIS6203) with the following overrides - 
 
//ALIS6230 EXEC PROC=ALIS6203,                                
//         DELREC=18000069200,16YYYYYYY00,16ZZZZZZZ00'       
//STEP0020.SYS004 DD *                                        
 POL=018000069200     CHANGE POLICY # ON THIS CARD - 12 DIGITS  
 
ï¿½	Requested PCD to rerun the job ALIS0030.
ï¿½	Requested PCD to rerun the job ALIS0050. 
Job ALIS0050 ended Ok with the above resolution. 

Firecall ID used:- P1SVBB

description:
CL$$0015 ENDED NOT OK_NO_CALL JOB NodeID: AUL1:
 Component : AUL1
close_notes:
system abend 0C7 occurred in module D7241007. At below cobol source code:
COBOL Source Code:                                                      
                                                                        
  Source                                                                
  Line #                                                                
  ------                                                                
      -5 CL7766     IF LICENSE-LOB-EFFECTIVE-DT(1:2) NOT = '99'         
      -4 CL7766        MOVE LICENSE-LOB-EFFECTIVE-DT(6:2) TO STANDARD-MM
      -3 CL7766        MOVE LICENSE-LOB-EFFECTIVE-DT(9:2) TO STANDARD-DD
      -2 CL7766        MOVE LICENSE-LOB-EFFECTIVE-DT(1:2) TO STANDARD-CC
      -1 CL7766        MOVE LICENSE-LOB-EFFECTIVE-DT(3:2) TO STANDARD-YY
  004385               CALL 'CKDCEXIN' USING STANDARD-DATE              
  004386                                     GSLAEFDT-APPOINT-EFF-DATE  
  004387 CL7191     ELSE                                                
      +1 CL7191       MOVE ZERO         TO GSLAEFYR-APPOINT-EFF-YEAR    
      +2 CL7191       MOVE ZERO         TO GSLAEFDY-APPOINT-EFF-DAY     
      +3 CL7191     END-IF.                                             
      +4            IF LICENSE-APPT-RENEW-DT(1:2) NOT = '99'            
      +5               MOVE LICENSE-APPT-RENEW-DT(6:2) TO STANDARD-MM   

Solution:

*We have found STSM8          CONTRACT          D5CNTRCT 2022-08-26-19.33.58.944652+001329106S in 
 IDIREPRT.
*We have checked this record in CL.CL$$0015.REPS.SORTED.G4023V00 file it seems fine.
* We have opened the CL.CL$$0015.REPS.SORTED.G4023V00 file and compared the every field with 
  AGLICENS copybook which we have found from D7241007 module. It seems some field entries are missing for abending record.
*So, we have put display's in program D7241007 at abending cobol source code for license line of business effective date and termination date which we found from and executed the abending STEP0050 in unit.
* We could see the License line of business effective date for all the records for STSM8 agent except for abending record.
* So we have skipped the record and executed the Job.

close_notes:
Hi All,
In CyberLife PROD cycle (Odate ï¿½ 08/09/22) Job CL$$0012 got abended at STEP0050 due to ABENDU0001.
 
As per spool :-

**********************************************************                      
* FUNDVAL ERRORS DETECTED FOR AUL                                               
**********************************************************                      
CEE3250C The system or user abend U 001 R=NULL     was issued.                  
         From compile unit CKABEND at entry point CKABEND at compile unit offset +00000118 at entry offset +00000118
         at address 00008788.                                                                                   

Analysis: 

There was an issue with Fundval date of CSBSF2 and and CSBS22 funds. Vul team corrected it and provided funds dates below:-
V00CSBS2210011080920220819202200005000000
V00CSBSF210011080920220819202200005000000

 
Solution :-
 
1) Rename the bad run GDG'S from CL$$0010 job :

CL.FUND.PRICES.CHANGED.G3492V00 - CL.FUND.PRICES.CHANGED.D081022
CL.BKUP.FUND.PRICES.G5861V00 - CL.BKUP.FUND.PRICES.D081022

CL.FUND.PRICES.SORTE2.G4318V00 - CL.FUND.PRICES.SORTE2.D081022
CL.CL$$0010.ERRRPT.G4277V00 - CL.CL$$0010.ERRRPT.D081022


3) Provided below restart instruction in the job CL$$0010 and asked OPS to run the job again from 'PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT' :

// RESTART=CL$$0010.STEP0045


4) Asked OPS to run the restore job CL$$R012 and then re run the job CL$$0012 from TOP.


Job Ended-OK with the above resolution.

Incident : INC0663056

Document referred : TEST.CL.BOMBLOG and SCHD.CTM.DOC

description:
In CK4 PROD Cycle (Odate -  08/08/2022), Job CK4$DW60 got abended at STEP0010 with ABEND=S0CB .

As per spool:

A system abend 0CB occurred in module D7341101 program CKULDBEN at offset     
X'CB2'.                                                                       
                                                                              
A program-interruption code 000B (Decimal-Divide Exception) is associated with
this abend and indicates that:                                                
                                                                              
  The divisor was zero in a signed decimal division.                          
                                                                              
 Abending policy  :

L52076958                                                                         

Analysis :

On further analysis found that ULGWDRPM-REFUNDED-PREMIUM gets calculates as 

COMPUTE ULGWDRPM-REFUNDED-PREMIUM ROUNDED =      
      FBRMPREM-MODE-PREMIUM                      
    / FBRBMODE-MODE * WS-DUE-MONTHS.             

Value of FBRBMODE-MODE is 000 which in turn results ULGWDRPM-REFUNDED-PREMIUM as decimal-divide exception.  

The refund amount of the death benefit is calculated through the program CKULDBEN in module D7341101 
 
COMPUTE ULGWDRPM-REFUNDED-PREMIUM ROUNDED =      
      FBRMPREM-MODE-PREMIUM                      
    / FBRBMODE-MODE * WS-DUE-MONTHS.     

So, CK4$DW60 calculates the refund amount of the death benefit by using CKULIV00. It does not calculate the refund amount of additional payment loan payment and rollover payment because it does not require the mode to be stored. Similarly, it should also exclude loan interest payment activity(PX) as it also does not require mode to be stored.
 
CK4$DW60 was abended for the policy L52076958 because this policy processed loan interest activity and the policy billing mode in 69 segment (activity segment) is zero which was not correct and will always result in ULGWDRPM-REFUNDED-PREMIUM filed as a decimal-divide exception.  
 
We made a fix in Program CKULIV00 when it locates the payment activity(69) also excludes loan interest payment activity(PX) whose fixed premium date equals paid-to-date


Resolution:

1)  Copied following files:-

CK4.SA.VSAM.BASEOL.ULIFINQ$ and CK4.SA.VSAM.BASEOL.AUXSEG1$ as

TEST.CK4.SA.VSAM.BASEOL.ULIFINQ$.P080822 and TEST.CK4.SA.VSAM.BASEOL.AUXSEG1$.P080822 respectively.



2) Bypassed the abending policy from backup file.


3) Provided following overrides-

//STEP0010.VSAM3 DD DSN=TEST.CK4.SA.VSAM.BASEOL.ULIFINQ$.P080822

//STEP0010.FVDSEG1 DD DSN=TEST.CK4.SA.VSAM.BASEOL.AUXSEG1$.P080822

4) Raised form to rerun the failed job from PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT library from TOP.
close_notes: CHG0076456 changes has been implemented in prod
short_description: CK4$DW60 - Death claim correction after loan interest payment

description:
Used Firecall ID TA04092 on date (0721) for resolving VCS$0111 Job failure

Please find Fire call usage details below:

a. The reason for the change - VCS$0111 Job failure
b. Fire call logon id - TA04092
c. The date the change was made - (0721)
d. The job was updated - we have Restarted the Job from TOP.
close_notes:
A system abend 0C7 occurred in module UNPACKP2 program PPLSUNP2 at offset      
X'3774'.                                                                       
Abending Policy:
G38910 ï¿½ Found based on the Instructions given in the below VCS$0111 abend notes.
\\slpfle01.oneamerica.com\vol_tm\Enterprise Compensation Tech Ref\On Call and Support Documentation\PPLUS  --- VCS$0111 Abend. 
Solution:
1.	Checked the file VCS.PPL.PPLUSHCH with HEX ON to see where numeric zeros are missing compared to adjacent rows. The policy number on the row where numeric zeros are missing should match the policy number found in IDIREPRT.
2.	Updated 9 sets of packed fields starting at column 114 (each set is made up of 4 numeric fields 3 bytes long, each denoted by the "C") and another 9 sets starting at column 394 using Fire call ID : TA04092
3.	Asked PCD to rerun the job from the top.
 
To Avoid VCS$0500 Job abend -
 
1.	Updated VarChar column:  TRANSACTION_IMAGE in PPLUS02.DSRPTRG table as the transaction is also available in this column.
2.	Updated 9 sets of packed fields starting at off-set 629 (each set is made up of 4 numeric fields 3 bytes long, each denoted by the "C") and another 9 sets starting at off-set 909 with numeric hex values by overlaying the spaces using Fire call ID : TA04092.

Job-Ended-OK with above resolution.

In last night's CyberLife PROD cycle (Odate ï¿½ 07/11/22), Job CL$$ABR1 failed at STEP0020 with ABENDU0888.

TMS014  IEF234E K 3236,023334,PVT,CL$$ABR1,STEP0020          
-STEP=STEP0020 PGM=FDRABR   ABENDED  - COND CODE  U888 RC=0000 RC=0000 ELAP=00:09:27.49 I/O BLKS=   1337897
IEF404I CL$$ABR1 - ENDED - TIME=22.21.47                     
Analysis and resolution:- 

As per Bomblog,  CL$$ABR1 was waiting on a Tape volume which was not available. Operation uses overrides for FDRABR. LastTape to stack Backup jobs on the same Tape. These files get deleted When ABR$9999 runs, which is normally after all ABR application backups are complete and before the vault job runs. Our job was trying to Stack on the tapes. Tape11 is the offsite Tape and was at the vault, Thus not available.

-	Asked PCD to restart the job from Top.
-	Job Ended-OK with the above resolution.
 
Incident: INC0655078
 
Document Referred: TEST.CL.BOMBLOG
 


Thanks & Regards,
Arya S R

close_notes:
Hi All,
In CyberLife PROD cycle (Odate -07/05/22) Job CL$$0165 got failed at STEP0110 with ABENDU1111
As per spool:-   

ADR412E (001)-DYNA (01), DATA SET CL.SA.VSAM.BASEOL.POLICY IN CATALOG CATALOG. AREA1 ON VOLUME STOR7A FAILED SERIALIZATION  
ADR801I (001)-DDDS (01), 2022.187 02:19:18 DATA SET FILTERING IS COMPLETE. 0 OF 1 DATA SETS WERE SELECTED: 1 FAILED SERIALIZATION

                          CL.VSAM.BASEOL.POLICY                                 
ADR006I (001)-STEND(02), 2022.187 02:19:18 EXECUTION ENDS                       
ADR013I (001)-CLTSK(01), 2022.187 02:19:18 TASK COMPLETED WITH RETURN CODE 0008
                                                  
Analysis:-

Dataset was used by job T004555 hence causing the abend. Asked the user to release the dataset.

ï¿½	Asked OPS to rerun the Job from the 'PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT' Library.
Job Ended-OK with the above resolution.

Document Referred: SCHD.CTM.DOC & On-call sheet.

description:
CL$$0012 Ended not OK_P1 CRITICAL JOB NodeID: AUL1:
 Component : AUL1
u_reason_for_reassignment: Other - Explanation required in work notes
close_notes:
Hi All,

In CyberLife PROD cycle (Odate - 06/02/22) Job CL$$0012 got abended at STEP0005 due to ABENDU0040 .

As per spool :-

IEF450I CL$$0012 STEP0005 CL$$0012 - ABEND=S000 U0040 REASON=00000000
STEP=STEP0005 PGM=XLEBMAIN ABENDED  - COND CODE  U040 RC=0000 ELAP= 00:00:23.68 I/O BLKS=  4493

Reason: -
Fundval file header date does not match with parmdate. SCHD1551 job has in condition "WAIT-4-DXC" the parmdate was not updated in the card, so we had remove the in condition and executed SCHD1551 and the parmdate got updated. 

And also Fund Prices file had incorrect date range for few funds.

We took the backup of fund prices file and updated the file with correct date.
Solution :-

1)We removed the in condition "WAIT-4-DXC"  from SCHD1551 job and it Ended-Ok.
2) Corrected the dates in fund prices file.
3) Had PCD ops to re-run the CL$$0012 Job from TOP.
Job Ended-OK with the above resolution.

Incident : INC0644822

firecall Usage logged under# INCTASK0011744

Document referred - TEST.CL.BOMBLOG 

Thanks,
Harindra
short_description: PCD- CL\$\$0012 Ended not OK_P1 CRITICAL JOB NodeID: AUL1

06-02@00:48:26 UTWAITDR: *I* Program UTWAITDR Begins execution at 06/02/2022 00

Usually we take help from PCD but we can check MQ queue from ourself also by following below steps.

close_notes:
Hi All,

In last night's CyberLife PROD cycle (Odate ï¿½ 04/25/22), Job CL$$EXT1 failed at STEP0020 with MAXCC = 0008.
 
Analysis and resolution:- 

Job CL$$EXT1 failed due to the unavailability of DB2 table - CLADMIN.OAS_PRDCR_VW

DSNT490I SAMPLE DATA UNLOAD PROGRAM                                            
 DSNT503I UNLOAD DATA SET SYSPUNCH RECORD LENGTH SET TO    80                   
 DSNT503I UNLOAD DATA SET SYSREC00 RECORD LENGTH SET TO    48                   
 DSNT504I UNLOAD DATA SET SYSREC00 BLOCK SIZE SET TO 27984                      
 DSNT493I SQL ERROR DURING SQL STATEMENT    FETCH   , TABLE CLADMIN.OAS_PRDCR_VW
DSNT408I SQLCODE = -904, ERROR:  UNSUCCESSFUL EXECUTION CAUSED BY AN UNAVAILABLE RESOURCE. REASON 00C90086, TYPE OF
         RESOURCE 00000200, AND RESOURCE NAME EDRM    .TPRDCRRO                 
DSNT418I SQLSTATE   = 57011 SQLSTATE RETURN CODE                                
DSNT415I SQLERRP    = DSNXRFF  SQL PROCEDURE DETECTING ERROR                    
DSNT416I SQLERRD    = -131  0  0  -1  0  0 SQL DIAGNOSTIC INFORMATION           
DSNT416I SQLERRD    = X'FFFFFF7D'  X'00000000'  X'00000000'  X'FFFFFFFF'  X'0000
         INFORMATION                                                            
                                                                                
We raised INCTASK0011346 for mainframe infra team and the issue was due to abend in job DB2$P213 so the contention was removed by infra team.

-	We renamed the already cataloged file CL.CL$$EXT1.TRIGGER.SEQUEN6 to TEST.CL.CL$$EXT1.TRIGGER.SEQUEN6.D042522.
-	Asked PCD to rerun the job from TOP.

 In 04/21/22 CyberLife PROD cycle job CL$$0600 failed at STEP0910 with  ABEND=S613 U0000.
Message from spool:
Please refer to the explanation in message IEC501E For Automated Tape Library dataservers                                                                  
(including Virtual Tape Servers), messages IEC501A and IEC501E are           
not issued to any operator console. They are only issued to the System       
Log.M indicates that a volume is to be mounted on the device:                
If ser is a 6-digit serial number, the volume                                
with that serial number is to be mounted on device dev.                      
If ser is SCRTCH, a public scratch volume is                                 
to be mounted. SCRTCH is used when the dataset being created on              
the non-specific volume is temporary ï¿½DISP=(NEW,DELETE) or DSN=&&tempnameï¿½.  
If ser is PRIVAT, a private scratch volume                                   
is to be mounted. PRIVAT is used for all other cases of non-specific         
volumes.                                                                     Solution:
ï¿½	Copied the Job from PROD.SCHD.JCLLIB to PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT Library.
ï¿½	Provided the below override in the job -
                           //             RESTART=CL$$0600.STEP0910,
                                //    STEP0910.SYSUT1 DD DSN=CL.CL$$0600.DST.FILES(0),  
            //                    DISP=(SHR,KEEP,KEEP)                 
ï¿½	Asked PCD operations to rerun the job from PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT Library.
ï¿½	Job-Ended-OK with above resolution. 
Document referred - TEST.CL.BOMBLOG, SCHD.CTM.DOC
 
Incident number - INC0632725

description:
CL$$0012 Ended not OK_P1 CRITICAL JOB NodeID: AUL1:
 Component : AUL1
u_reason_for_reassignment: Other - Explanation required in work notes
close_notes:
Hi All,

In CyberLife PROD cycle (Odate - 03/30/22) Job CL$$0012 got abended at STEP0005 due to ABENDU0040 and STEP0050 due to ABEND U0001.

As per spool :-

For  STEP0005:
IEF450I CL$$0012 STEP0005 CL$$0012 - ABEND=S000 U0040 REASON=00000000
STEP=STEP0005 PGM=XLEBMAIN ABENDED  - COND CODE  U040 RC=0000 ELAP= 00:00:25.31 I/O BLKS=      5023

For STEP0050:
IEF450I CL$$0012 STEP0050 CL$$0012 - ABEND=S000 U0001 REASON=00000000
STEP=STEP0050 PGM=D724FNDU ABENDED  - COND CODE  U001 RC=0000 ELAP= 00:00:10.52 I/O BLKS=3864

Reason: -
For STEP0005 
Fundval header date of CL$$0012 job does not match with parmdate. SCHD1551 job has in condition "WAIT-4-DXC" the parmdate was not updated in the card so we remove the incondition and executed SCHD1551 and the parmdate got updated.
For STEP0050:
Fund Prices file has processed incorrect date for few funds below:
We took the backup of fund prices file and updated the file with correct date.

Solution :-

For Step0005:
1)We removed the incondition "WAIT-4-DXC"  from SCHD1551 job.
2) Informed OPS to rerun the job from the top.

For STEP0050:
1) Ran the restore Job CL$$R012.
2) Took the backup of 'CL.BKUP.FUND.PRICES.G5770V00' as ' TEST.CL.BKUP.FUND.PRICES.D033022'
3) Updated the correct dates in the original file 'CL.BKUP.FUND.PRICES.G5770V00' using Firecall ID.
4) Informed OPS to rerun the job from the top.

Job Ended-OK with the above resolution.

Incident : INC0627414

firecall Usage logged under# INCTASK0011076
short_description: PCD- CL\$\$0012 Ended not OK_P1 CRITICAL JOB NodeID: AUL1

close_notes:
In ACTS TEST Cycle (Odate : 03/30/22) - Jobs ACTT0020 was Abended with S04C at STEP0090

Message from SPOOL :-
<H1> I B M   F A U L T   A N A L Y Z E R   S Y N O P S I S                   
                                                                                                                                                      
A user abend 0007 occurred in module CEEPLPKA at offset X'20A604'.          
                                                                            
The cause of the failure was program D684DM00 in module D684DM00.  The COBOL
source code that immediately preceded the failure was:                      
Source                                                                    
Line #                                                                    
------                                                                    
001997                CALL 'ILBOABN0' USING ABEND-U007.                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                             
Reason :- 
Dates were updated incorrectly in the master files ( The correct date should be 03/29/22 but it got updated as 03/30/22).

Solution :-
1) Took the backup of 5 master files 

2) Updated below master files Header date Manually from 20220330 to 20220329:-
TEST.ACTS.CLIENT.FILE.ACTFL
TEST.ACTS.DEPT.FILE.ADEPT
TEST.ACTS.MASTER.FILE.AMAST
TEST.ACTS.EXAM.MAILBOX.FILE.AMLBX
TEST.ACTS.TRACKING.FILE.ATRCK

3) As the time crossed 8 a.m.EST ,Updated following jobs to use hard-code dates 20220329 instead %%CURR.
ACTT0020 
ACTT0110
ACTT0130 
ACTT0150 
ACTT0200 
ACTT0210 

4) Provided below restart condition to ACTT0020 RESTART=ACTS0020.STEP0085.

5) Informed OPS to re-run the job with the above restart condition.
Job Ended Successfully

description:
CL$$ABR1 Ended not OK_NO_CALL JOB NodeID: AUL1:
 Component : AUL1
close_notes:
Hi All,

In last night's CyberLife PROD cycle (Odate ï¿½ 03/23/22), Job CL$$ABR1 failed at STEP0020 with ABENDU0888.

Message from spool:
TMS014  IEF234E K 302D,017796,PVT,CL$$ABR1,STEP0020         
-STEP=STEP0020 PGM=FDRABR   ABENDED  - COND CODE  U888 RC=0000 ELAP= 00:13:13.64 I/O BLKS=   1369458
IEF404I CL$$ABR1 - ENDED - TIME=22.23.18                    

Analysis and resolution:- 

As per Bomblog,  CL$$ABR1 was waiting on a Tape volume which was not available. Operation uses overrides for FDRABR. LastTape to stack Backup jobs on the same Tape. These files get deleted When ABR$9999 runs, which is normally after all ABR application backups are complete and before the vault job runs. Our job was trying to Stack on the tapes. Tape11 is the offsite Tape and was at the vault, Thus not available.

-	Asked PCD to restart the job from Top.
-	Job Ended-OK with the above resolution.
 
Incident: INC0625727
 
Document Referred: TEST.CL.BOMBLOG
 


Thanks & Regards,
Abhishek Jaiswal

close_notes:
In Cyberlife PROD night cycle (Odate: 03/14/22), Job CL$$0110 abended with ABEND S04C. 

Message from Spool:


IEC614I PRLSE FAILED - RC 016, DIAGNOSTIC INFORMATION IS (081

STEP0060,STOR50,CL.CL$$0110.STEP0060.ANZEXT                  
IEC216I A14-04,IFG0202E,CL$$0110,STEP0060,SEQUEN3,112E,STOR50
CL.CL$$0110.STEP0060.ANZEXT

IEC216I A14-04,IFG0202E,CL$$0110,STEP0060,SEQUEN4,1122,STOR38
CL.CL$$0110.STEP0060.FINEXT

Job has been abended multiple times due to DASD issue opening or closing or releasing the file. 
At first run the restore Job CL$$R110 from PROD.SCHD.JCLLIB Library. 

As per CTM doc, checked to clean up the GDG 'CL.CL$$0110.COMP.COMMSN(0)' created from bad run but it was not created so no action taken.

Restart the job from top but failed again.

Remove the RLSE parameter for abending file CL.CL$$0110.STEP0060.ANZEXT  then job got failed for another file CL.CL$$0110.STEP0060.FINEXT.

Again, run the restore Job CL$$R110 from PROD.SCHD.JCLLIB Library. 

Asked PCD to rerun the failed job from TOP again.

As per CTM doc, checked to clean up the GDG 'CL.CL$$0110.COMP.COMMSN(0)' created from bad run but it was not created so no action taken.

Remove the RLSE parameter for next abending file CL.CL$$0110.STEP0060.FINEXT.
Asked PCD to rerun the failed job from TOP again.

 Job CL$$0110 Ended OK with the above resolution.

description:
CL$$0600 ENDED NOT OK_NO_CALL JOB NodeID: AUL1:
 Component : AUL1
close_notes:
Hi All,
 
In 03/02/22 CyberLife PROD cycle job CL$$0600 failed with MAXX CC = 0020 at STEP0220.
 
Message from spool:
From STEP0220.SYSOUT ï¿½
 
PROBLEM READING ACF: 1 KEY: E 545003                      
APPLICATION TERMINATED DUE TO ACF**>> RUN ABORTED <<**    
POLICY = 2453396900                                       
 
Abending policy: 
2453396900
Solution:
ï¿½	Asked PCD to run restore job CL$$R600 from PROD.SCHD.JCLLIB Library.
ï¿½	Took the backup of file  CL.CL$$0600.ACTIVITY  into  CL.CL$$0600.ACTIVITY.D030222
ï¿½	As per bomblog, bypassed all the records for the abending policy from the original file : CL.CL$$0600.ACTIVITY
ï¿½	Renamed the below files which created in prior run - 
ï¿½	CL.CL$$0600.DFA.RECORDS  to  CL.CL$$0600.DFA.RECORDS.D030222
ï¿½	CL.CL$$0600.DST.DFA.FILE  to  CL.CL$$0600.DST.DFA.FILE.D030222
ï¿½	Copied the Job from PROD.SCHD.JCLLIB to PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT Library.
ï¿½	Provided the below override in the job -
                           //             RESTART=CL$$0600.STEP0220,
ï¿½	Asked PCD operations to rerun the job from PROD.SCHD.IND.CALLOUT Library.
ï¿½	Job-Ended-OK with above resolution.
 
Document referred - TEST.CL.BOMBLOG, SCHD.CTM.DOC
 
Incident number -  INC0615283
 
Firecall usage - INCTASK0010857

close_notes:

IGD17101I DATA SET RLRP.CW.EXT.NEXT.MONTH.INFAFB1        
NOT DEFINED BECAUSE DUPLICATE NAME EXISTS IN CATALOG     

Reason-A project that moved into production on Thursday did not have 2 files in a card member to be deleted. So job ran fine on Thursday night the first time files were created when they didn't exist. But then the job failed on Friday night since the files already existed.

Solution-Used ISPW to add these to lines

DELETE RLRP.CW.EXT.NEXT.MONTH.INFAFB1            NONVSAM SCRATCH PURGE      
DELETE SLRP.CW.EXT.NEXT.MONTH.INFAFB1            NONVSAM SCRATCH PURGE      

to PROD.FIN.CARDLIB(ABC12DEL)

Reran job from top. Job ended ok.
